title: For Sale:  LWRC IC-A5  (NEW IN BOX)
postcontent:
Directly descended from the rifles developed by LWRCI™ to meet the requirements for the U.S. Army Individual Carbine program, the IC-A5 is built for high performance. 
The IC-A5 is the latest model in the IC – Individual Carbine series. Customers called for an adjustable gas block and the longer 12” SPR style rail system on the same rifle. We listened- the IC-A5 is designed with a low profile 2 position adjustable gas block allowing the shooter to compensate for running a suppressor with the added benefit of our longer modular rail system.
The upper rail section on the IC-A5 is an aesthetically pleasing special cutback version which allows us to use the low profile gas block and at the same time keep the full 12” modular rails available on the sides and bottom of the hand guards. This IC-A5 brings together features of both the IC Enhanced and the IC-SPR in one package.
Like all IC models the IC-A5 is constructed using the highest quality materials, built on our patented self-regulating short-stroke gas piston system, machined from materials that belong to the super alloy family of steel alloys most often used in aerospace, LWRCI™ raises the bar on reliability and ease of maintenance- delivering the highest level of performance. The gas-piston system can be accessed quickly by loosening two thumb screws.
Dual Control fully ambidextrous lower receiver includes bolt catch and release, magazine release and fire control access from both sides of the IC-A5.  LWRCI™ Enhanced Fire Control Group comes standard.  Our investment castings are x-rayed for imperfections and nickel-boron coated for a smooth crisp trigger pull with positive reset. 
Our IC-A5 uses LWRCI™ manufactured- NiCorr treated cold Hammer Forged spiral fluted barrel that are 20% lighter than unfluted barrels of the same diameter.  The increased surface area reduces heat – speeds up cooling.  Nickel-boron coated bolt carrier delivers unparalleled wear resistance, corrosion resistance and permanent lubricity. 
The LWRCI™ IC-A5 comes complete with, LWRCI Skirmish™ Back Up Iron Sights, Ambidextrous Charging Handle, LWRCI™ Adjustable Compact Stock, Magpul® MOE+ Grip and A2 Birdcage flash hider.

title: For Sale:  Colt Model US Army Model 1917 45ACP Revolver  -- Original Finish
postcontent: For sale is a Colt U. S. Model of 1917 in 45 ACP cartridge.  This revolver has its original brushed finish with all frame and barrel markings clear and crisp.  The barrel is 5-1/2" long with clean, strong rifling.  U. S serial number is 339XX.  Research indicates this revolver was shipped 02/16/1918 to Ordnance Base Depot, U. S. Government, A. E. F. France, Ordnance Store #45, Bush Terminal, Brooklyn, N. Y.  This is one of 3600 revolvers in the shipment.  Originally these revolvers came with tapered chambers in the cylinder which required use of half-moon clips.  Above serial #30400, the chambers were given a shoulder to allow the 45ACP cartridge to be headspaced correctly and could be fired in an emergency without the half-moon clips.  The half-moon clips are still required for the ejector rod to work.  The Colt serial # for this revolvers is 184XXX.  I am not sure if the grips are original to this gun, but they do carry the Colt serial # written in pencil on the insides.  Overall, this revolver is in very nice condition.  Apparently this gun did not see service in WWII.  When removing the grips, a small hand-written slip of paper was found indicating the gun was purchased from Marshall Fields in Chicago on 4/2/42.  The buyer's and salesman's names are also listed.  Numerous photos available on request.  Price is shipped FFL to FFL.

title: For Sale:  Browning Hi Power 9mm Luger
postcontent: Browning Hi-Power 9mm Mark I Chinese contract pistol manufactured in 1945. This is one of the rare pistols that was actually sent to China. This particular gun was delivered to Shanghai in late 1945. The pistol is in excellent condition, although it appears to have been reparkerized at some point during its life. Armory refurbs were quite common. The gun is all matching and has it's lanyard and original magazine with aluminum follower and the split back floor plate. The pistol comes with a very nicely made wooden stock/holster, but after much research, I believe this stock to be a reproduction made by the Chinese in 1952. On the inside of the leather there is a stamp in Chinese characters which roughly translates to "Made in China 1952."

title: For Sale:  Browning BDM two-tone w/rare 15 round pre-ban mag
postcontent: Up for sale is my Browning BDM 9mm. These firearms were made between 1991-1998, and were actually designed to compete in the trials for the FBI's new service weapons. It didn't win, and was sold to civillans instead. It's a cool gun, with lots of awesome features that were way ahead of their time. The main one is the switch on the side of the gun, that switches the gun from SA/DA, to DAO. It's a feature implemented to try and ease police/agents away from revolvers and into semi-autos. Other cool features include a decocker/safety lever, and the fact that the frame where the grips are is actually cut out to make this grip even thinner than a Glock 19!It's extremely reliable, has a great trigger, and shoots whatever you put through it. It's definitely an amazing design...it was just way ahead of it's time. This firearm is in great condition, with just a few scratches and some wear which can be seen in the pictures. Mechanically, it's perfect and barely looks like it's ever been fired.This comes with two factory 10-round magazines (made during the ban era) and one EXTREMELY rare factory pre-ban 15 round magazine. I've only seen 2 of these pop up for sale and they were both listed at $150. In fact, there was one that sold on Gunbroker two weeks ago for $150+shipping which is a hefty price for a magazine!Also comes with the factory box and all original paperwork!The only two-tone models for sale right now are on Gunbroker, only have 10-round mags, and are listed at $575 & $699.I'm asking $500 FIRM for this, and that comes with the extra 15 round magazine. This price should be MUCH higher than it is. Priced low to sell fast, as always.***PRICE IS FIRM AND I DONT WANT TRADES. This is clearly stated in my ad, yet I keep getting lowball emails or trade offers from Armslist. Any trade offer or cash offer less than $500 will result in your number/email being blocked.No trades at this time, trying to recoup some of the money from all of my impulse buys the last few weeks.Located in Northville, willing to drive a bit but nothing crazy. Face to face only, no shipping.Must be 18+ w/Purchase Permit or CPL.Best way to contact me is by texting REDACTED at any time. Thanks for looking!~ Mike
